<section class="bio">
  <h2>Me in 10 seconds</h2>
  <p>I build and grow web products. Right now I work on growth and marketing-engineering projects at <a href="https://buffer.com" target="_blank">Buffer</a>. Before that I did marketing at a venture-backed startup called <a href="https://usertesting.com" target="_blank">UserTesting</a>.</p>

  <p>I thrive when I'm learning new things, practicing, and developing my skills - always trying to push myself just beyond what I'm currently capable of (I blame my old baseball coach for this).</p>

  <p>I think marketing, engineering, and design is an unstoppable combination of skills: a triple threat. I started my career in sales & marketing, and now I'm in the process of learning software engineering and product design.</p>

  <p>I <a href="/reading">read a lot</a> and love to study practical philosphy - particularly <a href="https://ryanholiday.net/stoicism-a-practical-philosophy-you-can-actually-use/" target="_blank">Stoicism</a> and <a href="http://www.bahai.org/action/" target="_blank">the Baha'i Faith</a>. Check out my list of <a href="/recommended-books">recommended books</a>.</p>

  <p><strong>What am I doing now?</strong> See <a href="/now">my "now" page</a>, which changes often.</p>
</section>

